AGI -&nbsp;Contested to the cry of "On my body I decide" to the general states of the birth, the Minister Eugenia Roccella failed to pronounce his intervention. After the contestation of the young people who have continued for a long time screaming "shameful shame", the 'fatherè&nbsp; of the house Gigi De Palo gave the word to one of the boys. One of them climbed on stage and read a flyer claiming words like "sex-affective education, words - he said - that they did not listen to any minister".
&nbsp;
And then he added: "On our bodies, we decide. The current government decides to convene this conference while none of the government, in a year, has answers to our demands. We are not at the triad God-father-family." De Palo, however, specified that "the event is convened by a Foundation and not by the government". When the girl finished reading the flyer and came down on stage, the ministra Roccella tried again to pronounce her intervention but at that point the "shame, shame" of the young people are resumed.
&nbsp;The ministra commented on the stage: "No one said that someone else decides on the body of women, indeed we are here because &nbsp; today women do not decide to the bottom of their body, if they can have children."
&nbsp;
The ministra turned from the disputes then went away.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Gigi De Palo, we hope not to throw work done
De Palo explained: "The ministra is gone and will return at another moment, hoping that this will calm the souls. We'll see tomorrow or in the next few days if we can recover." So, he added: "This event was organized with associations, schools, resources, notes, I ask you - he continued addressing journalists - to help us give the right weight to the news. We take a 10-minute break and hope not to throw all the work behind this event" the organizer concluded.
&nbsp;
"It is not acceptable that a small group of contestants prevented Ministra Roccella from speaking. The General States for Natality are a place that places the family at the centre, which has no political colors and that allows everyone to say their own" he added later in a press point - Concepts for us fundamental, so much so that we have exceptionally decided to overwhelm the program and let a representative of the contestants speak.&nbsp; It is not possible, however, that, despite this, there was no respect for them, institutional and personal, to make the Minister speak. I am absolutely supportive with her: I asked her to stay and answer but she, understandably shocked, decided to leave."&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Roccella, I expect solidarity from the podists of liberty
I am sure that the secretary of the Pd Elly Schlein, all the left, the intellectuals - Antonio Scurati, Roberto Saviano, Nicola Lagioia, Chiara Valerio, etc. -, the "big press" and the " militant press" that we have seen in these hours mobilized in other locations, will have unequivocal words of solidarity with me after the act of censorship that this morning has prevented me from speaking I am sure that the podists of freedom and democracy will not miss this opportunity to demonstrate that the evocation of fascism that is not there, to which we have witnessed in these weeks, was not only a political scene ready to fade in front of the real census". So on Facebook the Minister for the Family, Eugenia Roccella, after the contests this morning to the general states of birth.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Bipartisan tradition in Roccella</h2>
"My solidarity with the Minister of the Family, the Birth and Equal Opportunities, Eugenia Roccella, forced to leave the general states of Christmas without having to keep their intervention." Francesco Lollobrigida explains that "fear that those who claim the right to decide do not let a minister of the Republic freedom to express their ideas". "My thoughts also go to the organizers and to the many women, present and future mothers, to whom it was not allowed to expose one's own thought", adds the exponent FdI, with the party that makes square in support of Roccella while solidarity statements arrive also from Iv and Action.<br> "What happened this morning to the general states of birth is unqualified." The Minister for Christmas, Family and Equal Opportunities, says Ester Mieli, Head of FdI Equal Opportunities and Policies against all discrimination.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Eugenia Roccella was forced to leave the stage - resumes - due to the disputes of a group of people. Precisely those who profess democracy have become protagonists, once again, of an attitude of censorship towards those who do not think it like them. I express solidarity with Minister Roccella by encouraging her to carry out her work in favour of families, birth and women." "Everyone has the right to express their opinion, it is always wrong to give way to attacks, hatred and violence. To the ministra Roccella all my solidarity," adds.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Licia Ronzulli notes that "there is no more illiberal way of claiming freedom by preventing you from speaking with protests, screaming and whistling, forcing a minister to abandon an event." "And it is even more serious and unacceptable the method, unfortunately frequent, to sabotage the manifestations of others. I wish to express to Minister Roccella all my solidarity," concludes Vice President FI of the Senate.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"It is serious that the Roccella Minister had to give up intervention in the general states of birth, to her my full solidarity," says Maria Elena Boschi.<br> The exponent of Italia Viva adds that "the expression of dissent is lawful, but it cannot be forgotten that freedom and democracy are expressed first of all allowing to speak, not with censorship".
&nbsp;
"Italy is sick of a mad ideology that wants to deny evidence, truth and nature. There is an emergency, a demographic winter that, if it does not end, risks making the Italian nation disappear within a few generations. It is a reality that is current, undeniable. It must be taken note and, with responsibility, it must be put remedy through a policy in favor of families and of the birth", says Senator FdI Roberto Menia.
&nbsp;
"Being children of a nation - he resumes - also means feeling the desire to perpetuate it without need of genetic engineering and renting uters: This is what happens from the night of time through the union between a man and a woman who form a family. No one decides about the body of others, no violence and no coercion. Free will, free will and responsibility. There's someone who understands and who doesn't. Solidarity with Minister Roccella."
<br> "Contesting an orator preventing his intervention is an unacceptable form of violence for a democratic country," says Vice-Chairman Nm at the House, Pino Bicchielli. "To the general states of Christmas - he resumes - was given to the group of protesters who contested the minister of the Family every opportunity to expose his point of view, but the purpose instead was to suffocate the voice of Eugenia Roccella, which after vain attempts to expose his own point of view was nothing left to do but to abandon the stage first, then the Auditorium. We are close to the ministra Roccella, we condemn abuse and we hope that this is not the way in which debates and conferences will take place in the future, on the theme of birth or other topics". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
