AGI -&nbsp;It is in stable conditions although critical the policeman Christian Di Martino>, attacked and stabbed> to the back in the night at the Lambrate station in Milan>. The 35-year-old deputy inspector was operated in the night at the Niguarda hospital to contain the bleeding caused by the three phendents in the back. Doctors have not yet dissolved prognosis. The arrested man, of Moroccan nationality, is called Hasan Hamis.&nbsp;He served from 9 June 2020 to 4 July 2023 a sentence to 3 years of imprisonment for robbery and lesions> in the prison of Ariano Irpino (Avellino). The 37-year-old, irregular, expiated, had received an order of expulsion issued by the Irpine police. The first control in Italy dates back to 2022 while the last, on 5 May, at the Bologna station > where the railway police denounced him for the possession of a razor with which he would threaten them and some passengers on board a train.&nbsp;
<h2> The story
Around midnight last, this reconstruction, the Railway Police requested the intervention of the policemen of the Police of the Police of Milan for the presence of a man in a strong state of agitation who, while he was near the railways in the station, was throwing stones against trains and people and had hit the head a woman, Italian of 55 years, then transported in green code at the hospital Fatebenefratelli.
&nbsp;
Two patrols arrived and the man, "in evidently altered and uncooperative mental state", was struck with the taser, >"without however that the discharge had had effectiveness because of the jacket that the same one wore".
&nbsp;
A colluctation was born and the 37-year-old struck with three back defenders the 35-year-old Deputy Inspector of the State Police with three back defenders. The attacker is now at the San Vittore prison.

